	   <tr><td colspan=2>There is better out there, but it's a decent belt.  <br><br>I recieved mine during the Lfay event involving Firiona Vie, Equestrielle, and the Avatar of Cazic Thule.  I was picked out of a crowd numbering over a hundred people, so I was somewhat surprised to say the least (But then, I had been following that GM event series from start to finish so it may not have been accidental).  <br><br>I recieved a coin (forget the name, it's been so long) which I turned in, per GM instruction, to Lord Nethrin the Arbitrator in Felwithe.  This was the reward.  <br><br>The coins are NO RENT, but seem to be tradeable, I have completed the Realm of Heroes quest twice, and have recieved this belt and the Heartsinger Earring.  Though in the future I think I may attempt to give the coin to a character who would benefit more from the item than myself.  It would at least be a worthy experiment.<br><br>If you are not at the point of doing high end Velious quests or Temple of Veeshan, these items are as good as you are going to find in the pre-Luclin game.  If you are at or past that point, you may still want to attend GM events in hopes of an artifact being handed out.  <br><br>Cheers and Good Luck.<br><br>Merril Starshine<br>54th Cavalier of Tunare<br>Cazic Thule Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
